    "created_at": "2015-07-01T15:43:12Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-01T15:51:41Z",
    "body": "I did a little test with:\n\n```\nsetInterval(function(){\n        console.log( mainWindow.isAlwaysOnTop() );\n    }, 1000);\n```\n\nEven when I have managed to cause another app window to overlay the app window that is set to be always on top (mainWindow), the console still returns true... so electron thinks the window is still on top... even when it's not! Any ideas?\n"
  },
