    "created_at": "2015-07-07T02:38:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-07T02:38:15Z",
    "body": "The `always-on-top` option is a hint to operating system or window manager that this window should be put above all non-topmost windows, and it is allowed to have top-most windows overlapping each other on most systems.\n\nSee also [How do I create a topmost window that is never covered by other topmost windows?](http://blogs.msdn.com/b/oldnewthing/archive/2011/03/10/10138969.aspx).\n"
  },
