    "updated_at": "2016-12-08T20:23:30Z",
    "body": "is there an electron setting that can make an always-on-top window appear ABOVE a fullscreen app?  let's say that we launch some child process which goes into fs mode (real fs, not fs-windowed).  I know that windows is capable of still placing something over it, but is *electron* capable of asking windows to do this?"
